This race was about gratitude for me. I am grateful for my past, I am grateful for what God has done for me this year, and I am grateful that I have unlimited potential - just like you do. 

Philippians 4:13 I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me. 

This year I said at the beginning in my new years resolutions video I posted: that I was going to pursue a community in my faith, that my business was going to grow and that I was going to level up my fitness. That video rang in my ears all year through my decision-making processes, and through the relationships I have formed over this past year, I’m now seeing what’s possible differently. 

I hope you’ve seen possibility through my posts this year, I hope you’ve felt encouraged, and I hope you declare some things over your life this month to change to make 2023 your best year yet!

Unleash Your Potential: The Art of Stretching! 

What I’ve found over the past year and a half since I’ve been on my running / #hybridathlete training is that there is a secret weapon never to skip - stretching, and here's why you shouldn't either!

💥 Elevate Your Performance: Stretching isn't just about flexibility; it's a performance enhancer. It primes your muscles for action, reduces the risk of injury, and boosts power output. 

💥Muscle Mastery: Want to maximize muscle growth? Stretching increases blood flow, ensuring your muscles get the nutrients they need to grow and recover faster.

💥Vital Circulation: Improved blood circulation means more endurance, quicker recovery, and better workouts. 

So, don't underestimate the power of stretching! It’s a 10-minute habit you can build into your day to help every area of your training. 

Here’s a quick routine I use: 

- touch toes 
- child’s pose 
- pigeon pose 
- lunging hamstring stretch 
- kneeling quad stretch 
- kneeling lunge stretch 
- figure 4 stretch 
- seated or laying spinal twists 
- roll out 

Make it a cornerstone of your fitness journey, and watch how much better it helps you feel and perform! 

#stretchtosuccess #fitnessmotivation #mindbodyspirit
